<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-030-054 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 432 625</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Oct 22 1991 v5 n36 p18(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Savvy software can send ZIPandplus;4 codes. (Semaphone Corp.'s ZP4address-correction software)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rothenberg, Matthew.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Semaphore Corp. (Product enhancement).andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (Computer programs)ZP4 (Data base) (Product enhancement).andO;Topic:     AddressingSoftware PackagesData BasesEnhancements.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Matthew RothenbergandM;Aptos, Calif.andP;  -- Semaphore Corp. has posted an update to its ZP4address-correction software package that makes use of a high-level System 7Apple event.andM;ZP4, a Mac-compatible database of U.S.andP;  addresses, automatically standardizesmailing lists and adds ZIPandplus;4 codes, the enhanced ZIP code system requiredwhen sending mail via the U.S.andP;  Postal Service's discounted &quot;automation&quot;rates.andM;According to Semaphore, its new high-level event protocol lets users send anaddress from within any System 7-savvy application; ZP4 will correct theaddress and send it back to the original program.andP;  The source code for thisprotocol is available free from Semaphore, the company said.andM;Updated every three months on a subscription basis, ZP4 includes streetsuffixes, post office-standard city names, carrier-route numbers and ZIPandplus;4codes.andP;  The package holds more than 28 million records and includes the namesof more than 1.2 million companies and organizations that have their ownZIPandplus;4 codes.andM;ZP4 uses official data files from the U.S.andP;  Post Office, which has certifiedthe program's accuracy.andM;ZP4 is available on CD-ROM for $125 per quarter; on floppy disks, thedatabase software is $99, and address information is $49 per quarter forregional postal information.andM;Semaphore Corp. is at 207 Granada Drive, Aptos, Calif.andP;  95003-5007.andP;  Phone(408) 688-9200; fax (408) 662-2717.andO;</TEXT></DOC>